<collectingRegion box="[1228,1324,324,350]" country="Sweden" name="Uppsala" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Uppsala</collectingRegion>
and is considered lost. However, in the SMNH are several lots from the Atlantic that may have been part of Bovallius’s original material. Fortunately the descriptions and figures of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bovallius, C." box="[264,478,444,470]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref35551" refString="Bovallius, C. (1887 c) Contributions to a monograph of the Amphipoda Hyperiidea, Part I: 1. The families Tyronidae, Lanceolidae and Vibilidae. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 21 (5), 1 - 72, pls 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1887">Bovallius (1887c)</bibRefCitation>
readily characterise this species. No precise 
<typeStatus box="[1030,1080,444,470]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
locality is given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bovallius, C." box="[264,468,484,510]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref35487" refString="Bovallius, C. (1887 a) Systematical list of the Amphipoda Hyperiidea. Bihang till Kungliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Handlingar, 11 (16), 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1887">Bovallius (1887a</bibRefCitation>
, c). He merely lists the distribution as “Atlantic, Indian Ocean” (1887a), and “North Atlantic, tropical Atlantic” (1887c).
</paragraph>
